      <tr><td colspan=1  style='font-size: 9.5px;'>571 threads, <a href=classes.html?class=13&start=0>1</a> <a href=classes.html?class=13&start=25>2</a> <a href=classes.html?class=13&start=50>3</a> <a href=classes.html?class=13&start=75>4</a> <a href=classes.html?class=13&start=100>5</a> <a href=classes.html?class=13&start=125>6</a> <a href=classes.html?class=13&start=150>7</a> <a href=classes.html?class=13&start=175>8</a> <a href=classes.html?class=13&start=200>9</a> <a href=classes.html?class=13&start=225>10</a> <a href=classes.html?class=13&start=250>11</a> <a href=classes.html?class=13&start=275>12</a> <a href=classes.html?class=13&start=300>13</a> <a href=classes.html?class=13&start=325>14</a> <a href=classes.html?class=13&start=350>15</a> <a href=classes.html?class=13&start=375>16</a> <a href=classes.html?class=13&start=400>17</a> <a href=classes.html?class=13&start=425>18</a> <a href=classes.html?class=13&start=450>19</a> <a href=classes.html?class=13&start=475>20</a> <a href=classes.html?class=13&start=500>21</a> <a href=classes.html?class=13&start=525>22</a> <a href=classes.html?class=13&start=550>23</a>  page(s) long</td><td  style='font-size: 9.5px;' align=right>&nbsp;<a href=classes.html?class=13&start=25>Next Page</a></td></tr></table></form><a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13>Root thread</a><table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=10265236122833></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10265236122833><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>RE: Elexxie</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43653><span id=Scholar>GLASS</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>161 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jul 12th 9:38 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.43]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>QUOTE:<br><br>&quot;I personaly like playing my chanter because I get respect for the stuff I pull of.&quot;<br><br><br><br>I couldn't agree with that statement more.&nbsp;&nbsp;Last night I had two of those 'Proud to be an Enchanter' moments.  The first one was the coolest.  My friend (39 wizzy) and I (46 ENC) were running through EW to camp Snow Griffins for the 3rd shawl quest.  We were almost to our camp when our sows both ran out and invis had popped off some time before.  Rather than stop to recast we decided to keep going since we were so close.<br><br>We got jumped first by a wolf who conned green to me.  No problem.  I shoot one stun at him and by that time I get aggroed by a snow dervish also, blue to both of us.  So, I hit both with the second AoE stun and back off to mezz one.  I decide to mezz the derv first since he's currently targeted and the higher conning of the two.  So, the wizzy roots the wolf and is about to start nuking when I see a snow griffin directly behind him and closing fast.  As quickly as I can warn him the griff is on the wizzy like stink on a wood elf.  Griffs hit hard (~109 or so from what I've seen) and fast.  A 39 wizzy doesn't last long.  His HP were falling VERY fast and I barely got mezz to land on the griff before he bit the dust.  I could see nothing but the tiniest sliver of red in my partners health bar.  <br><br>&quot;GATE!!!&quot;  I say, and turn and start a mezz on the wolf who is only rooted up until now.<br><br>&quot;I don't have it memmed.&quot;<br><br>&quot;Well mem it, you got time.&quot;<br><br>&quot;I'm stunned.&quot;<br><br>&quot;HAHA!&quot;<br><br>Well, the stun finally wore off and he sat down to mem gate, still not even a step away from the griff that had him all but lying down three seconds earlier.  About the time I get the wolf mezzed and am about ready to sit down to mem gate myself, I get aggroed by yet another MOB, this time a snow cougar, also conning blue to me.  Again I throw two color spells at him and back off to try and get the mezz off.<br><br>Of course he resists my first mezz (nothing is easy in life and just when you think you've got it made something goes wrong), but after two more stuns and the second attempt he is standing there helpless.<br><br>In all this time the first two of the four mezzes had worn off, and I can only thank the stars (I'm agnostic) for the mem blur effect mezz has.  Otherwise I would have been toast.  Well, the wizzy made it out while I was wrestling with the last cougar, and after I got him under control I finally had enough time myself to memorize gate and get the hell outta dodge.  I only had one bub of hit points myself by that time.<br><br>I don't think of myself as a 'great enchanter' or anything like that.  I think that anybody could have handled that situation as well or better than I.  I just think it kicks ass to have the capability to allow two unarmored, defensively puny players who are outnumbered 2 to 1 to safely evade an otherwise hopeless battle.<br><br><br><br>The second cool event is a bit shorter and not as cool.  It was actually earlier in the night when we were still collecting ulthork meat.  It seemed to be 'feast or famine' pulling up there.  There were either ulthorks everywhere or none to be seen.  So, as I went out to pull, I saw one (blue), tashed it, saw another (light blue), ran by and aggroed him, and saw a third (another blue)which I also picked up.  With sow I came back to the wizzy and had enough room to mezz the first one in line, then ran a quick loop to get enough room to mezz another.  Meanwhile, the wizzy rooted the third and went to work on him.<br><br>Once I got the two parked, of course I sat to med and refreshed the mezzes as needed. As soon as the wizzy said go, we released the second and I got one nuke off while still keeping the third parked.<br><br>The point of this story?  I just thought it was pretty damn cool that a group of two could get away with a triple pull, albeit with a few med breaks in there.  Still, not many class combinations could have done this.<br><br>This is why I love being an enchanter!<br><br>Have fun.<br><br>-Yizz<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
